    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Headlight
        System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Floor-Mounted Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and International Engine
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Headlight System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Floor-Mounted Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and
            International Engine
        </title>
        <table id="t0824013" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Headlight System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Floor-Mounted Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and
                International Engine
            </title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.56in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F26 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F26, and at circuit 14F measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26, 14F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (35) and at circuit 50, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), 50 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 50, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test headlight switch (35) by placing switch in headlight on position, and
                                measuring resistance from term. 1 to 2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), term. 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective headlight switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (17) and reconnect connector (35). With headlight switch still
                                on, measure voltage at (17) from circuit 51F to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), 51F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 51F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (17), going to floor- mounted dimmer switch, measure resistance from
                                green wire to blue wire with the switch in dim position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(17), green wire to blue wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (17), going to floor- mounted dimmer switch, measure resistance from
                                green wire to brown wire with the switch in dim position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), green wire to brown wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (2) and reconnect (17). With headlight switch still on, move
                                dimmer switch to dim position and at (2), measure voltage from circuit 53 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(2), 53 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (502) and (504) and reconnect (2). With switches still set, at
                                (502), measure voltage from circuit 53B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(502), 53B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(504), 53A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (502) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53B to
                                11-GC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(502), 53B to 11-GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GB or 11-GC, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to 11-GE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(504), 53A to 11-GE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GB or 11-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move headlight switch to headlight position and dimmer switch to high beam position.
                                Disconnect connector (2) and measure voltage from circuit 52 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(2), 52 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With connectors (502) and (504) still disconnected and switches still set, reconnect
                                conn. (2) and at (502) measure voltage from circuit 52C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(502), 52C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 52B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(504), 52B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Head- light circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
